ove of human beings, the conceptual structure of love, friendship, misanthropy, and the highest good. The contributors include internationally well-known experts in the field. They approach the topics diversely from historical, philosophical, critical, and interpretative perspectives. The collection will be an invaluable resource for Kant scholars and for anyone interested in affective social relations in the history of philosophy and beyond.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 4aEhe. 4aKant, Immanuel. 4aMoral. 4aSexualität. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Modern.2bisacsh  aKant, Immanuel.  amarriage.  amorality.  asexuality.1 aBhardwaj, Kiran, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrecher, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrecher, Martin, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGrenberg, Jeanine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLouden, Robert B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoran, Kate, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRinne, Pärttyli, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRinne, Pärttyli, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSchönecker, Dieter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSeymour Fahmy, Melissa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z978311117578208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook pa